 "Enter an RSS URL for the RSS feed you \nwant to attach to your content. Feeds are often identified by a small graphic\n icon (often like this <img src=\"\/images\/feed-icon.png\" \/>) or the text \"RSS\". Clicking on the \n icon or text label will display an RSS feed right in your browser. You can copy and paste the\nURL into this field. Alternately, right clicking on the link or graphic will open a menu box;\nclick on COPY LINK LOCATION or Copy Shortcut. Back in eXe open the RSS bookmark iDevice and Paste the URL \ninto the RSS URL field and click the LOAD button. This will extract the titles from your feed and\ndisplay them as links in your content. From here you can edit the bookmarks and add\n instructions or additional learning information.": "Indtast en RSS URL til den RSS link du \n\u00f8nsker at vedh\u00e6fte til dit indhold. Et RSS link kan ofte identificeres af en lille grafisk\n ikon (ofte som dette <img src=\"\/images\/feed-icon.png\" \/>) eller teksten \"RSS\". Ved at klikke p\u00e5 \n ikonet eller teksten vil der vises en RSS link til h\u00f8jre i din browserr. Du kan kopiere og inds\u00e6tte \nURL'en i dette felt. Alternativt h\u00f8jreklik p\u00e5 linket eller grafikken, der vil s\u00e5 \u00e5bnes en menuboks;\nklik p\u00e5 KOIPER LINK PLACERING eller Kopier Genvej. Tilbage i eXe \u00e5bner du RSS bogm\u00e6rket iDevice og Inds\u00e6t  URL'en \ni RSS URL feltet og klik INDL\u00c6S knappen. Dette vill udtr\u00e6kke titlerne fra dit RSS link og\nvise dem som links i dit indhold. Herfra kan du editere bogm\u00e6rkerne og tilf\u00f8je\ninstruktionerne og tilf\u00f8je information til indl\u00e6ring.", 
